reactor.core

Interface Dispatcher

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Executor, Resource
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractLifecycleDispatcher, MpscDispatcher, MultiThreadDispatcher, NettyEventLoopDispatcher, RingBufferDispatcher, SingleThreadDispatcher, SynchronousDispatcher, TailRecurseDispatcher, ThreadPoolExecutorDispatcher, TraceableDelegatingDispatcher, WorkQueueDispatcher

    public interface Dispatcher
extends Executor, Resource
    A Dispatcher is used to dispatch(Object, Consumer, Consumer) dispatch} data to Consumers. The details of how the dispatching is performed, for example on the same thread or using a different thread, are determined by the implementation.
    Author:
    Jon Brisbin, Andy Wilkinson, Stephane Maldini

    • Method Detail

      • dispatch

        <E> void dispatch(E data,
                  Consumer<E> eventConsumer,
                  Consumer<Throwable> errorConsumer)
        Instruct the Dispatcher to dispatch the data. The event Consumer will receive the event. In the event of an error during dispatching, the errorConsumer will be called.
        Type Parameters:
        E - type of the event
        Parameters:
        data - The event
        eventConsumer - The consumer that is driven if dispatch succeeds
        errorConsumer - The consumer that is invoked if dispatch fails. May be null
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - If the Dispatcher is not alive

      • tryDispatch

        <E> void tryDispatch(E data,
                     Consumer<E> eventConsumer,
                     Consumer<Throwable> errorConsumer)
              throws InsufficientCapacityException
        Instruct the Dispatcher to dispatch the data. If the dispatcher doesn't have enough capacity and might block on the next produced event, The event Consumer will receive the event. In the event of an error during dispatching, the errorConsumer will be called.
        Type Parameters:
        E - type of the event
        Parameters:
        data - The event
        eventConsumer - The consumer that is driven if dispatch succeeds
        errorConsumer - The consumer that is invoked if dispatch fails. May be null
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - If the Dispatcher is not alive
        InsufficientCapacityException

      • remainingSlots

        long remainingSlots()
        Request the remaining capacity for the underlying shared state structure. E.g. RingBufferDispatcher will return RingBuffer.remainingCapacity().

        Returns:
        the remaining capacity if supported otherwise it returns a negative value.
        Since:
        2.0

        Returns:
        the remaining capacity if supported otherwise it returns a negative value.
        Since:
        2.0

      • supportsOrdering

        boolean supportsOrdering()
        Inspect if the dispatcher supports ordered dispatching: Single threaded dispatchers naturally preserve event ordering on dispatch. Multi threaded dispatchers can't prevent a single consumer to receives concurrent notifications.
        Returns:
        true if ordering of dispatch is preserved. * @since 2.0

      • inContext

        boolean inContext()
        A dispatcher context can be bound to the thread(s) it runs on. This method allows any caller to detect if he is actually within this dispatcher scope.
        Returns:
        true if within Dispatcher scope (e.g. a thread). * @since 2.0
